MBOMBELA &#8211; Bullet, the Lowveld&#8217;s most famous (living) dog, celebrates his first birthday today.The Australian cattle dog is one of two belonging to Bossies Community Justice&#8217;s (BCJ) crime-fighting team. The other is a border collie named Patch. Bullet is undergoing training to assist BCJ in the field.When Bullet arrived in the Lowveld, he was still a puppy.BCJ is a non-profit organisation whose main objective is to enable faster reaction and response times when life-threatening incidents or emergencies arise within Mbombela and the greater Lowveld. BCJ works closely with the police and other crime prevention and crime-fighting organisations.Four things you didn&#8217;t know about Bullet:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;What Bullet does not like, is crime.If you are not a fan of crime either, you can contribute to the BCJ cause.Phone Albert Gryvenstein on 082-567-5212